<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As sales of appetite-suppressing drugs such as=
=C2=A0Ozempic=C2=A0and Mounjaro skyrocket, Corporate America is grappling w=
ith the question: How does a less-hungry, less-impulse-prone consumer affec=
t my business model?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Companies from=C2=A0Walmart Inc.=C2=A0to=C2=A0=
Conagra Brands Inc.=C2=A0are weighing how much to factor the diabetes drugs=
 known as=C2=A0GLP-1s, increasingly being used for weight loss, into their =
strategies. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">John Furner, CEO of Walmart=E2=80=99s US opera=
tions, recently=C2=A0said the retailer is seeing=C2=A0a =E2=80=9Cslight pul=
lback in the overall basket=E2=80=9D of food purchases as a result of the d=
rugs, but added it=E2=80=99s too early to draw definitive conclusions. Cona=
gra CEO=C2=A0Sean Connolly=C2=A0told investors this week that his company=
=E2=80=99s scientists are looking at the data, and the maker of Slim Jim an=
d Swiss Miss could offer smaller portions in the coming years if that=E2=80=
=99s the way preferences evolve. =C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The comments have helped to drive a=C2=A0react=
ion in the market, driving the=C2=A0S&amp;P 500 Consumer Staples Index=C2=
=A0down 0.5% on Friday. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re still learning what els=
e it might be good for,=E2=80=9D said Daniel Drucker, a co-discoverer of th=
e GLP-1 hormone who works as a professor of medicine at the University of T=
oronto. =E2=80=9CThis is brand-new territory.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am not a scientist but I feel like some of w=
hat I read about these drugs suggest that they <em>are </em>almost=C2=A0uni=
versal demand suppressants, or at least that they are good at suppressing a=
 lot of addictive behavior. Snacking, drinking, smoking, but what about scr=
olling Instagram or clicking online ads? Sure it starts with Slim Jims, but=
 does it end there?</p>
