or: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>=C2=A0he refused. So now the SEC has gone to court,=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0<=
/em>to fine him for violating the disclosure rules, but to force him to com=
e in to talk:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission (=E2=80=
=9CSEC=E2=80=9D) announced that it has filed an application seeking an orde=
r directing Elon Musk (=E2=80=9CMusk=E2=80=9D) to comply with an investigat=
ive subpoena calling for his appearance for testimony, with which Musk fail=
ed to comply. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the filing, Musk failed to appear=
 for testimony as required by the investigative subpoena served by the SEC,=
 despite: (1) agreeing to appear for testimony on a mutually agreed upon da=
te in September 2023; (2) having been served with a subpoena in May 2023 re=
quiring his appearance for testimony in the SEC=E2=80=99s San Francisco Reg=
ional Office on that mutually agreed upon date; and (3) raising no objectio=
n to the subpoena from May 2023 until two days before his scheduled testimo=
ny date in September 2023, when Musk notified the SEC that he would not app=
ear. According to the filing, Musk attempted to justify his refusal to comp=
ly with the subpoena by raising, for the first time, several spurious objec=
tions. =C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32969259.256422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saXRp=
