 new documents produced by Musk. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In light of the substantial new information th=
e SEC obtained following Musk=E2=80=99s last half-day session of testimony,=
 in April 2023, the SEC staff discussed with Musk=E2=80=99s counsel the nee=
d for Musk to appear for another day of testimony.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The point here is that=C2=A0actually Musk=C2=
=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>come in to talk to the SEC, twice,=C2=A0in July 2022, =
a few months after the investigation kicked off. I don=E2=80=99t know what =
happened there? Maybe:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>SEC:</strong> It says in your disclosu=
re that you had bought 5% of Twitter by March 14, is that right?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> I guess.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>SEC:</strong> So 10 days after that wo=
uld be March 24, right?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> Ooh look at you, a lawy=
